This paper deals with privacy attacks on location data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves data analysis and machine learning techniques to understand and mitigate these attacks, which could fall under sub-categories such as social and information networks (cs.SI), databases (cs.DB), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the privacy-utility trade-offs of different defenses, which could also fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
